{% spaceless %}

<div class="pure-u-1 ODRContentWrapper">
    <div class="ODRThemeElement">
        <div class="ODRInnerBox">

            <div id="ODRMarkdown_content" class="ODRAccordionWrapper ODRTabAccordion">
                <div id="ODRMarkdown_tabheader" class="pure-u-1 ODRTabButtonHeader">
                    <button class="pure-button ODRTabButton" rel="emphasis">Emphasis</button>
                    <button class="pure-button ODRTabButton" rel="headings">Headings</button>
                    <button class="pure-button ODRTabButton" rel="links">Links</button>
                    <button class="pure-button ODRTabButton" rel="lists">Lists</button>
                    <button class="pure-button ODRTabButton" rel="code">Code</button>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2"><h1>Text using Markdown syntax</h1></div>
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2"><h1>Text viewed in a browser</h1></div>
                </div>

                <div id="ODRMarkdown_emphasis" class="ODRFieldArea pure-u-1">
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <textarea class="ODRMarkdown_source" id="ODRMarkdown_emphasis_source" readonly>
## Emphasis

Using a _single_ \* or \_ character creates _italic_ text.

Using **two** \* or \_ characters in a row creates __bold text__.

Using ___three___ \* or \_ characters in a row creates ***bold and italic*** text.

You **can _also_ combine** one __type of *emphasis* inside__ another.

Placing a \\ character before the \* or \_ characters will cause them \*\*to not\*\* be interpreted for emphasizing text.
                        </textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <div class="ODRMarkdown_result" id="ODRMarkdown_emphasis_result"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="ODRMarkdown_headings" class="ODRFieldArea pure-u-1">
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <textarea class="ODRMarkdown_source" id="ODRMarkdown_headings_source" readonly>
## Headings

The # symbol at the beginning of a line denotes a heading.

# h1 Heading
## h2 Heading

You're allowed to use up to six # characters in a row, but most websites (ODR included) tend to use specific styling for those elements.

___
Three hyphens, underscores, or asterisks in a row creates a horizontal line

---
Text right above three hyphens is a shortcut for the h2 Heading
---
                        </textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <div class="ODRMarkdown_result" id="ODRMarkdown_headings_result"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="ODRMarkdown_links" class="ODRFieldArea pure-u-1">
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <textarea class="ODRMarkdown_source" id="ODRMarkdown_links_source" readonly>
## Links

Typing something like [this](http://www.opendatarepository.org) will create a link.

You can also create a [link](http://www.opendatarepository.org "sample tooltip") that displays a tooltip when hovering over it.
                        </textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <div class="ODRMarkdown_result" id="ODRMarkdown_links_result"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="ODRMarkdown_lists" class="ODRFieldArea pure-u-1">
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <textarea class="ODRMarkdown_source" id="ODRMarkdown_lists_source" readonly>
## Lists

Unordered

+ Create a list by starting a line with `+`, `-`, or `*`
+ Sub-lists are made by indenting 2 spaces:
  - Marker character change forces new list start:
    * Praesent dapibus id libero sit amet consectetur
    + Proin nec libero ac orci aliquet elementum
    - Nullam venenatis ligula vitae justo facilisis rutrum
+ Very easy!

Ordered

1. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
2. Nulla sem tortor, cursus id accumsan a, aliquam viverra mi
3. In convallis arcu nisl, ac tempor eros tempus vel
                        </textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <div class="ODRMarkdown_result" id="ODRMarkdown_lists_result"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="ODRMarkdown_code" class="ODRFieldArea pure-u-1">
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <textarea class="ODRMarkdown_source" id="ODRMarkdown_code_source" readonly>
## Code

Inline `code block`

Block code "fences"

```
var a = 5;
var b = 10;

var c = a + b;
```
                        </textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
                        <div class="ODRMarkdown_result" id="ODRMarkdown_code_result"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

{% endspaceless %}
